Without stepping into another board wargame vs computer wargame debate
here, I'll say that yes, I use VASSAL almost exclusively for gaming
now days (currently pbem'ing &quot;Fire in the Sky&quot; and ASL (using VASL -
www.vasl.org )).  I have 13 modules uploaded to the site that I've made
and another 4 or 5 that I'm working on (in various states of
completion).  The program is well supported with new features being
added all the time (it just recently went through a major upgrade from
version 2.99 to 3.0x).  VASSAL was the tool that made me go back and
look at my old board wargames- which has led to some compulsive
shopping for new games.  :)

Also, check out Cyberboard: http://cyberboard.brainiac.com/ and
ZunTzu: http://www.zuntzu.com .  The latter program has particularly
interested me with it's smooth scrolling, zoom and animated dice
features.  Very well done program - doesn't support pbem play though
unfortunately.
</POST>
