I'm a big Vassal user and supporter.
I'm currently playing a few games of ASL, Monmouth and Europe
Engulfed.
I've contributed a few modules and have worked on the base code to
clean up image scaling.  Added a few features such as the &quot;Map View&quot;
function, I think I stole the little globe icon from some old version
of Mosaic.  ;)
I hate having to sit and wait for my opponent to make decisions in
face to face play.  At least with Vassal I can go somewhere else while
I'm waiting, much more time efficient.

Sadly, the code base is somewhat clunky and hard to decipher;
Features which really should be easy to add can be painfully time-
consuming.  As much as I love Java, for apps such as this I think the
platform specific .NET would have been better suited.
</POST>
